name: Dying a little each time someone calls it "Blockbusters"
description:
Anachronistic memories of stucco-clad suburban strip mall hellholes. Renting one VHD and shoplifting another in case the first one sucks. Always returning both, we're not animals.

We're not animals. Not like them.

Cold sweats & hot flashes in the checkout line. They make their money on the snacks man, it's a trap. Be strong.

Just then, she turns and looks at you as if to say, "We're not walking to the convenience store NEXT DOOR to buy candy are we? Let's just get something here."

Just throw the money on the fucking ground why don't we.

[collab w/ diewiththemostlikes]
